  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-6 min or until softened but not coloured </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-and-saffron-risotto-with-rocket/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion softens, dissolve the <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>vegetable stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and <strong>saffron</strong> in 700ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1.4L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-and-saffron-risotto-with-rocket/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, stir the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> into the pan and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil </p>\n<p>Add the<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for 30 sec further</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-and-saffron-risotto-with-rocket/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1/3 of the<strong> stock </strong>and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it has absorbed into the rice </p>\n<p>Continue to add the <strong>stock</strong>, a ladle at a time, stirring more or less continuously for 20-25 min, until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-and-saffron-risotto-with-rocket/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, cut the<strong> lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p>\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>\n<p>Pat the <strong>hake</strong> <strong>fillets</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season both sides with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-and-saffron-risotto-with-rocket/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>hake</strong>, skin-side down, and cook for 4-5 min or until the skin has started to crisp</p>\n<p>Flip the fish and cook for 1-2 min further or until cooked through</p>\n<p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-and-saffron-risotto-with-rocket/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the <strong>risotto</strong> from the heat and stir in the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheese</strong> and a very large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>juice</strong> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lemon </strong>and season very generously with <strong>pepper</strong> (use much more than you normally would!) – this is your <strong>saffron risotto</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the risotto is looking a little dry</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-and-saffron-risotto-with-rocket/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>saffron risotto</strong> in bowls, topped with a handful of <strong>rocket</strong> and the <strong>pan-fried hake</strong></p>\n<p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
